description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Digital Dictation team based at Monkwearmouth Hospital. We have two positions available as shown below, and other hours to cover shifts may also be available on an ad hoc basis. Shifts available are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tuesday 3pm - 7pm (4 hours) and Friday 9pm - 7am (9.5 hours) - 13.5 hours total&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tuesday 5pm - 9pm (4 hours) and Saturday 9pm - 7am (9.5 hours) alternate weeks with the other weeks requiring Saturday 3pm - 9pm (6 hours). 13.5 / 10 hours alternate weeks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties of the role will include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audio Typing (at least 50wpm)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proof Reading&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use of our patient information system (Rio) and other systems to save data to patient records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shift work &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, you should have experience of working in the NHS, and be able to work both independently and as part of a team, with a good working knowledge of Microsoft Word, Excel and Outlook. Flexibility and dedication is essential as this is a 24/7 service operating 365 days per year with set turnaround times for work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the current pandemic, successful applicants would be expected to work from home rather than from our usual hospital site office based. You must ensure you have the space and set up to allow comfortable and safe home working. This arrangement may change in the future, IT equipment will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All jobs will be appointed on NTW Solutions terms and conditions (not NHS terms)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date for applications will be 19th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For all enquires please contact Alison Lathan, Digital Dictation Admin Lead on 07467338913 or Chris Stewart, Head of Performance and Transcription Services on 07825792189.  &lt;/p&gt;
